---
---

<section id="the-problem" class="relative py-28 px-6">
  <!-- Subtle divider glow -->
  <div class="absolute top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[400px] h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-amber/20 to-transparent"></div>

  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-16 reveal">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-text mb-4">
        Simulation is only as good as its <span class="italic text-amber">data</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg max-w-xl mx-auto">
        The bottleneck isn't compute — it's the data going in.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <!-- Card 01 -->
      <div class="reveal reveal-delay-1 p-6 rounded-xl border border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] bg-bg-card">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-amber/60 tracking-wider mb-4 block">01</span>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mb-3">Objects aren't simulation-ready</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Most 3D assets lack the physical properties — mass, friction, collision geometry — that simulators need for accurate grasping, stacking, and manipulation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 02 -->
      <div class="reveal reveal-delay-2 p-6 rounded-xl border border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] bg-bg-card">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-amber/60 tracking-wider mb-4 block">02</span>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mb-3">Environments don't exist at scale</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Training mobile robots requires thousands of diverse, physics-accurate worlds. Building them by hand takes months and doesn't cover edge cases.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 03 -->
      <div class="reveal reveal-delay-3 p-6 rounded-xl border border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] bg-bg-card">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-amber/60 tracking-wider mb-4 block">03</span>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mb-3">Variety is the real bottleneck</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Domain randomization demands endless variations of objects and scenes. Without scalable 3D data generation, the sim-to-real gap stays wide open.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
